seedlings.name: Meru-oak (Vitex keniensis)
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Grows in altitudes of 1200-2100m, Mean annual rainfall of 900-3000mm, Prefers deep sandy-loam soils
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Grows 12-30m tall, 3m diameter, has a thin bark, rough and slightly fissured

seedlings.name: Mango tree
seedlings.environmental_conditions: A warm environment with ideal temperatures of 21°C
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Deep taproot and profuse surface roots, stout trunk (90cm in diameter) and an umbrella-shaped crown that may reach 20-40m high

seedlings.name: Avocado
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Warm 60-80°F, humid climates of about 60-80% humidity
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Elliptic to egg-shaped leaves (4-12 inches), tall or spreading, small, greenish flowers borne in inflorescence

seedlings.name: Eucalyptus (Tasmanian blue gum)
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Leaves are long, slender and hang downwards, on a single stalk, flowers have fluffy white or red buttons

seedlings.name: Outeniqua yellowwood (Afrocarpus falcarpus)
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Sandy-loam soils, Mean annual rainfall of 900-3000mm, Elevations of 1200-2100m above sea level
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Grows up to 25m tall, gray and often purplish bark, small, stiff lance-shaped leaves

seedlings.name: Iroko tree (Milicia excelsa)
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Plenty of sunlight, well draining soils

seedlings.name: Glaucum (Sequoiadendron giganteum)
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Can tolerate reduced light levels to some extent, prefers deep, well-drained loamy soils, annual precipitation 900-1400mm
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Uniformly scale-like leaves, reddish-brown fibrous bark, Can grow to 83m and 31m circumference

seedlings.name: African tulip tree
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Thrives in abundant sunlight, Requires plenty of moisture, Soil fertility and drainage are necessary for healthy growth
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Can grow up to 20m, Crown is thick and dark in color, Stem diameter can reach up to 60 cm, Bark is smooth and gray brown when young & cracks vertically and horizontally gradually darkening over time

seedlings.name: Macadamia nut
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Thrives in full sun 6-8hrs a day, Well-draining slightly acidic to neutral soils, Warm, wet climates of between 61°F-77°F
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Can grow up to 18m high, Can spread out to about 15m wide, Leaves are shiny, leathery and about 20-30 cm in length, When mature each fruit cluster can contain up to 20 nuts

seedlings.name: African redwood tree
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Thrives in full sunlight for optimal growth, Prefers well drained soils, Are resilient to climate changes
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Can grow up to 20m in height, Has a short trunk with thick branches and thick, peeling bark, Leaves are compound with 7-13 leaflets each about 10 cm long

seedlings.name: Mahogany
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Needs well draining soils rich in organic matter, Prefer abundant rainfall, high humidity and warm temperatures, Their presence contributes to overall health and biodiversity of tropical rainforests
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Compound and alternate pinnate leaves, dark green and shiny leaves on the upper surface and paler on the underside, small, fragrant, white or pinkish flowers, Fine wood, known for its straight fine grain and durability

seedlings.name: Moringa tree
seedlings.environmental_conditions: Needs a bright, sunny location for adequate sunlight, well draining and sandy soils, soil should be consistently moist, Temperatures should be between 77°F-95°F
seedlings.botanical_characteristics: Can reach up to 9m tall, Has a corky gray bark hence a distinct appearance, bi or tripinnately compound leaves, oval-shaped leaflets, scented pea-like flowers with five stamens
